    {
        _selectedValues.Clear();
        foreach (var item in newSelectedValues)
        {
            _selectedValues.Add(item);
        }
    }
}
```

So the user is setting `SelectedValues` initially to `{"test1"}`. And the `Comparer` is `StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase`.

Let me think about this more carefully. With strings, `EqualityComparer<string?>.Default` uses ordinal comparison. "test1" equals "test1" ordinals. So the dictionary lookups should still work...

Unless the issue is that the `SelectedValues` parameter comparer uses `SequenceComparer` (line 66) which uses the `Comparer`, and the comparison detects the values as "changed" somehow...

